## A15 Backend API Extensions
**Status:** draft
**Tags:** stack:backend, module:project

```rust
// GET /api/forge/specs/{project}/goals/tree
// Returns goals in hierarchical structure
pub async fn get_goals_tree(
    State(state): State<AppState>,
    Path(project): Path<String>,
) -> Result<Json<GoalsTree>, AppError> {
    let specs = state.specs_store.load(&project)?;
    let goals = specs.sections.iter()
        .find(|s| s.section_type == SectionType::Goals)
        .map(|s| &s.items)
        .unwrap_or(&vec![]);
    
    let mut tree = GoalsTree::new();
    
    // Build tree structure
    for goal in goals {
        let parsed = parse_goal(goal);
        
        if let Some(parent_id) = &parsed.parent_id {
            tree.add_child(parent_id.clone(), parsed);
        } else {
            tree.add_root(parsed);
        }
    }
    
    Ok(Json(tree))
}

// POST /api/forge/specs/{project}/goals/validate
// Validates goal ID format and parent references
pub async fn validate_goal(
    State(state): State<AppState>,
    Path(project): Path<String>,
    Json(goal): Json<SpecItem>,
) -> Result<Json<ValidationResult>, AppError> {
    let mut errors = Vec::new();
    
    // Check ID format
    if !VALID_ID_REGEX.is_match(&goal.id) {
        errors.push("Invalid ID format".to_string());
    }
    
    // Check parent exists
    if let Some(parent_id) = &goal.parent_id {
        let specs = state.specs_store.load(&project)?;
        let parent_exists = specs.sections.iter()
            .find(|s| s.section_type == SectionType::Goals)
            .map(|s| s.items.iter().any(|g| g.id == *parent_id))
            .unwrap_or(false);
        
        if !parent_exists {
            errors.push(format!("Parent goal {} not found", parent_id));
        }
    }
    
    // Check depth (max 1 level)
    if goal.id.matches('.').count() > 1 {
        errors.push("Max hierarchy depth is 1 level (G9.1 is ok, G9.1.2 is invalid)".to_string());
    }
    
    Ok(Json(ValidationResult {
        valid: errors.is_empty(),
        errors,
    }))
}
```

```typescript
interface GoalsTree {
  roots: GoalNode[]
}

interface GoalNode {
  id: string
  title: string
  status: Status
  priority?: string
  tags: Tag[]
  children: GoalNode[]
  expanded: boolean  // Default: false
}
```

- Frontend receives pre-built tree structure (no client-side tree building)
- Validation ensures data integrity (orphans, circular refs, depth)
- API is idempotent (same data, same tree)

